HEADWORD: Cerebropathy
<hw>Cer`e*brop"a*thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cerebrum</ets> + Gr. <?/ suffering.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A hypochondriacal condition verging upon insanity, occurring in
those whose brains have been unduly taxed; -- called also <altname>brain
fag</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

